summaries.short: The Doom Patrol embraces their inner morons after receiving a mysterious package.
summaries.full: Miranda helps protect the Doom Patrol from some truly terrible ideas after a mysterious package arrives at Doom Manor. Rita’s visit to the Cloverton beekeeper leads her to confront her lingering mommy issues. While on his way back to the manor, Cliff ends up stuck on the side of the road, literally. Niles heads north to find Dorothy’s mother.

summaries.short: Jane sets out to prove her worth. Cliff goes into "dad mode." Niles devotes a day to Dorothy, who’s finally growing up.
summaries.full: Determined to prove her worth in The Underground, Jane brings Larry to rural Arkansas to help her retrieve an invaluable item. Niles organizes a special day for Dorothy, who hides a personal development from her declining father. Cliff gives father-daughter bonding with Clara his best shot, while Rita embraces her superhero status as "The Beekeeper" and Vic is forced to confront the real Roni.

summaries.short: Niles’ old research team returns from space, and Dorothy goes missing.
summaries.full: Larry is tasked with handling Niles’ old research team when the ageless aeronauts return from space. As Niles and Cliff set out to find a missing Dorothy, a funeral in The Underground occupies Jane’s mind. Meanwhile, Vic discovers a curious connection between Roni and S.T.A.R. Labs, and Rita finds that her role in an upcoming community theater production hits too close to home.

summaries.short: Before the Doom Patrol can answer a call to save the world, they must first battle long-forgotten imaginary friends.
summaries.full: Before they can save the world from The Candlemaker, the Doom Patrol must first confront their childhood imaginary friends. Meanwhile, Jane reflects on the first time that Miranda became primary, and Dorothy must make a fateful choice.

summaries.short: Dorothy finds a friend in Baby Doll, while Vic looks to win Roni back. With Rita’s help, Larry finally tries to break the ice with his family.
summaries.full: Dorothy finally finds a friend in Baby Doll, until playtime goes awry. Cliff discovers that Niles plans to give him human-like upgrades. Vic devises a plan to win Roni back. After Rita has a lousy audition, Larry brings her along to meet his family and learns more about the life he left behind.

summaries.short: Dorothy and the Candlemaker finally face-off, while the Doom Patrol – now freed from their wax encasings – face troubling side effects. Rita holds the key, but is she ready to answer the call?
summaries.full: After Dorothy and the Candlemaker’s ultimate showdown, the Doom Patrol confront various troubling complications from being freed of their wax encasings. Entrusting Rita with a secret she may not be ready to handle, Niles is then pursued by a mysterious woman from his past.

summaries.short: When the Dannyzens arrive at Doom Manor to save Danny the Brick, Flex Mentallo helps Rita release her mental block and, incidentally, much more.
summaries.full: When the Dannyzens throw a massive party at Doom Manor to resuscitate Danny the Brick, Dorothy longs to join the festivities and experience life as a grown-up. As the party rages on, Rita asks Flex Mentallo to help unleash her full potential, which has some dangerously racy consequences.
